body:
Thanks for taking the time to report this.

Can you please attach an example that shows the issue or missing feature?  (Must be openly licensed, completely self-contained so can directly run what you provide. Ideally use test_regress format, see https://veripool.org/guide/latest/contributing.html?highlight=test_regress#reporting-bugs)

```
module p_i_match #(
  parameter type             S_IS_T,
  parameter S_IS_T      S_IS
) (
);
endmodule  
module ring #(
  parameter int unsigned   N_IS           = 16,          
  parameter int unsigned   N_IS_PER_S = 2,          
  parameter type           I_T
) (
);
   localparam int unsigned N_SS   = (N_IS / 2) / N_IS_PER_S;
   localparam int unsigned N_P_IS = (N_IS / 2) - (N_IS_PER_S - 1);
   typedef int s_is_t [N_P_IS-1:0];
   function automatic int i_plus_delta ( int i, int delta);
      i_plus_delta = 0;
   endfunction
   function automatic s_is_t gen_s_is (bit reverse);
      for (int st=0; st < N_SS; st++) begin
         for (int i=0; i < N_IS_PER_S; i++) begin
             if (st*N_IS_PER_S + i < N_P_IS) begin
                int delta = ((st+1)*N_IS_PER_S) + i;
                gen_s_is[st*N_IS_PER_S + i] = i_plus_delta( 0, reverse ? -delta : delta);
             end
          end
       end
   endfunction
   localparam s_is_t     S_IS = gen_s_is(0);
   p_i_match #(
      .S_IS_T    ( s_is_t ),
      .S_IS      ( S_IS )
   ) p (
   .* );
endmodule
module tb_ring;
   localparam int N_IS           = 18;
   localparam int N_IS_PER_S = 2;
   localparam int I_W            = 5;
   typedef logic [I_W-1:0] i_t;
   ring #(
      .N_IS          ( N_IS ),
      .N_IS_PER_S( N_IS_PER_S ),
      .I_T           ( i_t )
   ) dut ( .* );
endmodule
```

What output from that test indicates it is wrong, and what is the correct or expected output?  (Or, please make test self-checking if possible.)

```
verilator --binary test.v
%Error: Internal Error: test.v:29:33: ../V3Width.cpp:2957: InitArray type not assigned by AstPattern/Var visitor
                                                      : ... note: In instance 'tb_ring.dut'
   29 |    localparam s_is_t     S_IS = gen_s_is(0);
      |                                 ^~~~~~~~
```

What 'verilator' command line do we use to run your example?

```
verilator --binary test.v
```

What 'verilator --version' are you using?  Did you try it with the git master version?  Did you try it with other simulators?

```
Verilator 5.041 devel rev v5.040-367-gaf2771e90
```

What OS and distribution are you using?

```
Linux 5.14.0-570.37.1.el9_6.x86_64
```

May we assist you in trying to fix this in Verilator yourself?

(Please avoid attaching screenshots that show text - you can convert images to text using e.g. https://ocr.space)

